{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Dash (by Plotly)\n      Python-only, Plotly-native, full HTML/CSS control\n      Write Python, get real HTML components. Full CSS customization, no fighting the framework. Plotly charts work natively (zero serialization overhead). Mature ecosystem with dash-mantine-components for polished UI elements.\n      \n        Pros\n          Full HTML/CSS — you own every pixel\n          Plotly is native (already your chart library)\n          Stays 100% Python\n          dash-mantine-components = polished out of box\n          Production-ready (used at scale by enterprises)\n        \n        Cons\n          Callback model is different from Gradio\n          Slightly more boilerplate than Gradio\n          Need to add dash as dependency","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1774858795728}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      NiceGUI\n      Python, Vue.js-based, Tailwind CSS, modern feel\n      Python framework built on Vue.js + Quasar components. Tailwind CSS for styling. More modern-feeling than Gradio with better customization. Auto-reload during dev.\n      \n        Pros\n          Very Pythonic API\n          Tailwind CSS built-in\n          Modern Vue.js components\n          Easy to learn from Gradio\n        \n        Cons\n          Plotly needs integration wrapper\n          Smaller community than Dash\n          Less battle-tested at scale","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1774858797563}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      FastAPI + Custom HTML/JS\n      Maximum control — hand-crafted frontend served by Python backend\n      FastAPI serves a REST API. Frontend is hand-written HTML/CSS/JS with Plotly.js for charts. Total design freedom. Can look like anything — Apple, Linear, Bloomberg Terminal.\n      \n        Pros\n          Absolute design freedom\n          Fastest possible UI (no framework overhead)\n          Can achieve any aesthetic\n          Impeccable /frontend-design applies perfectly\n        \n        Cons\n          Must write HTML/CSS/JS by hand\n          More code to maintain\n          Need to handle API calls, state, etc.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1774858809508}
